BHV_Scout
=========

This behavior replaces random scouting with deterministic coverage of the
convex RESCUE_REGION. It evaluates horizontal and vertical boustrophedon
routes, starts from the lowest-cost direction, and uses fresh NODE_REPORT data
to bias the initial route toward territory contested by another scout.

Every SCOUTED_SWIMMER report is immediately sent to the configured rescue
teammate as an offboard SWIMMER_ALERT. The coverage pass repeats in reverse so
missed probabilistic detections receive another opportunity without a long
reset transit.

Parameters
----------
  tmate           Required rescue teammate name
  desired_speed   Scout speed in m/s (default 1.6)
  capture_radius  Waypoint capture radius in m (default 5)
  lane_spacing    Coverage grid spacing in m (default 28)
  contact_timeout Maximum age of opponent reports in seconds (default 20)
